<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4581500>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 3. Alυinocaris muricola Williams, 1988. Left thoracic appendages. (A) Third maxilliped, lateral; (B) coxa and antepenultimate segment of third maxilliped, dorsal; (C) first pereopod, lateral; (D) carpus of first pereopod, mesial; (E) second pereopod, lateral; (F) chela of second pereopod, dorsal; (G) third pereopod, lateral; (H) dactylus of third pereopod, lateral; (I) fourth pereopod, lateral; (J) fifth pereopod, lateral; (K) dactylus of fifth pereopod, lateral. Female from Régab site, west equatorial African margin (CL 16.8 mm; MNHN-Na 14277)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4581500/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4581534>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 18. Alυinocaris sp. 1. (A) Right antennal scale, dorsal (marginal setae omitted); (B) right first pereopod, lateral; (C) chela of right first pereopod, outer; (D) right third pereopod, lateral; (E) dactylus and distal part of propodus of right third pereopod, lateral. Allotype female of Alυinocaris stactophila Williams, 1988 from Bush Hill hydrocarbon seep, Gulf of Mexico (CL 6.8 mm; USNM 234293)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4581534/files/figure.png" .

